Use the standard library
This is how to triangle_area of a and b and c:
   Remember that ab is sum of a and b
   Remember that ac is sum of a and c
   Remember that bc is sum of b and c
   When ab is at most c, then:
      The answer is -1
   End when
   When ac is at most b, then:
      The answer is -1
   End when
   When bc is at most a, then:
      The answer is -1
   End when
   Remember that s is quotient of (sum of (sum of a and b) and c) and 2
   Remember that area2 is product of s and (product of (diff of s and a) and (product of (diff of s and b) and (diff of s and c)))
   The answer is sqrt of area2
Now you know